configurator.models.name: IoT
configurator.models.desc: An Internet of Things sample that illustrates the possibilities to integrate a digital model with physical sensors installed on real equipment. In that demo the first four sensors in the list are returning fake data generated on the fly, it can be connected with a fifth sensor that displays along the others. Once a sensor is selected, the graphs will show realtime data sent by that sensor representing current temperature, luminosity and acceleration.

configurator.models.name: ScreenShot Manager
configurator.models.desc: A panel illustrating the use of viewer.getScreenShot API: take screenshots of the desired size and save them to disk by clicking on the thumbnail.

configurator.models.name: Fader
configurator.models.desc: Forge Fader is a WiFi signal attenuation simulator: user can pick the position of the router on the floor and the signal strength will be represented by a custom shader on the surface. The signal strength is computed based on the attenuation in air and per wall depending the distance and number of walls between the position and the signal source. Parameters can be modified by user and we also included a cool 'dynamic' mode ...

configurator.models.name: Level Filter
configurator.models.desc: Computes building levels based on floors components and lets user toggle display for specific level.

configurator.models.name: Model Loader
configurator.models.desc: Multiple model aggregation extension for the Forge Viewer, which lets you load and unload models to the same scene. Also included as part of the demo, the Model Transformer extension allows you to translate, rotate and scale models at will.

configurator.models.name: Selection Filter
configurator.models.desc: A custom TreeView component that controls selectability of the model entities. Toggle each switch in the tree to enable/disable selectability of the component: disabling a parent component will automatically disable all children. The TreeView is implemented in plain JavaScript manipulating the DOM API but each node content is rendered by React

configurator.models.name: Visual Reports MFG
configurator.models.desc: The MFG version of the Visual Reports demo. The extensions set is slightly different than its AEC counter-part: ForceGraph is a cool feature pulled out from D3, BarChart and PieChart represent visually the categorized selected model component properties.

configurator.models.name: Particle System
configurator.models.desc: A custom 3D particle system written in JavaScript integrated with the Forge Viewer. Have fun tweaking the parameters of the emitters and magnetic fields to see the effect on the spinning particles!

configurator.models.name: Plant Factory
configurator.models.desc: A large plant factory model integrated with D3 graphs and data tables representing visually some of the available model component properties.

configurator.models.name: Wall Analyzer
configurator.models.desc: A demo that performs a geometric analysis of the loaded model based on the Floors and Walls component categories in order to display wall meshes at each level of the building.

configurator.models.name: Config Manager
configurator.models.desc: Create sequences of viewer states and store them in database. Each state can be restored independently or played as a loop in the sequence. States can also be hooked to custom extensions, like ModelTransformer and Markup3D in that demo.

configurator.models.name: Showcase
configurator.models.desc: Showcase a model: this demo creates a skybox around a model and adds some controlled camera motion. Camera position can be moved by user but target is always pointing at the model. After a while without user interactionthe motion will be restored.

configurator.models.name: Physics
configurator.models.desc: Live physics simulation in the browser! An integration of Ammo.js (an ASM.js emscripten port of Bullet Physics C++ library) with the Forge Viewer. Probably the fanciest sample on that gallery, check it out now if you haven't seen it yet!

configurator.models.name: Kinematics
configurator.models.desc: Hierarchical transforms combined with web animation.

configurator.models.name: Selection Window
configurator.models.desc: Custom Selection Window Extension: select components visually using a 2D selection window defined on the screen.

configurator.models.name: Extension Manager
configurator.models.desc: That panel controls loading & unloading viewer extensions. Click on the items to toggle the extensions ON or OFF. Each extension script is dynamically requested from the server first time is has to be loaded, illustrating advanced feature management in a large real-world Web Application. You can choose below between Custom Extensions (various demo extensions from FPD Team) and Native Extensions (Official extensions provided along Forge Viewer API).

configurator.models.name: Markup 2D
configurator.models.desc: A demo editor to control the Markup 2D API: create and save sequences of viewer states including SVG data from the markups that be be restored at a later time at your will or replayed in order.
